FBIS3-38505 "drweu023__a94003" FBIS-WEU-94-023-A Document Type:Daily Report 3 February 1994 ANNEX Inter-European Affairs Cotti, Danish Foreign Minister Discuss EU Membership BR2801152894 Bern ATSA/SDAA in French 1702 GMT 27 Jan 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY BR2801152894 Bern ATSA/SDAA Language: French Article Type:BFN [Article signed MA; SN; SH: "Flavio Cotti Meets With Danish Foreign Minister; European Union at Heart of Discussions"; as released by Bern ATSA/SDAA database] [Text] Zurich, 27 Jan (ATSA) -- Federal Council member Flavio Cotti and Danish Foreign Minister Niels Helveg Petersen held a two-hour discussion on international issues on Thursday afternoon [27 January] in Zurich. At the news conference afterward at Zurich-Kloten Airport, Mr. Cotti declared that Denmark had assured Switzerland of its support in the bilateral negotiations with the European Union [EU]. Mr. Petersen has welcomed the Swiss strategic goal of joining the EU. The Danish foreign minister believes this will facilitate bilateral negotiations. Denmark and other countries will be pleased to see Switzerland join the EU, the Danish minister said. He feels the Danish experience proves that small countries have at their disposal important possibilities to act within the EU.
